Courier Corp said it expects toreport a small loss for the second fiscal quarter against aprofit of 828,000 dlrs a year ago.    The company attributed the loss to competitive pressureswhich have cut gross margins. In addition, it said it isincurring significant expenses from management programs aimedat reducing costs and boosting productivity.    It said its Murray Printing Co unit has undertaken aprogram of extended work hours, and salary and job cuts whichwill save more than 1.5 mln dlrs annually. Reuter&#3;